  "body": "### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe annotation @Blocking on a gRPC service method should not run on an event loop thread, which works great. But when we add a @RolesAllowed annotation to use an authentication mechanism, the @Blocking does not seem to work anymore, and the method is running on an event loop thread.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected the gRPC service method with the annotation @Blocking and @RolesAllowed to be not running on an event loop thread.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nBut the gRPC service method with the annotation @Blocking is running on an event loop thread.\r\n\r\n### How to Reproduce?\r\n\r\n[https://github.com/TheImpressiveDonut/grpc-quarkus-blocking-bug](https://github.com/TheImpressiveDonut/grpc-quarkus-blocking-bug)\r\n\r\nExplained in the README.md\r\n\r\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\r\n\r\nMicrosoft Windows [Version 10.0.22621.1848]\r\n\r\n### Output of `java -version`\r\n\r\njava version \"19.0.1\" 2022-10-18\r\nJava(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 19.0.1+10-21)\r\nJava HotSpot(TM) 64-Bit Server VM (build 19.0.1+10-21, mixed mode, sharing)\r\n\r\n### Quarkus version or git rev\r\n\r\n3.1.3.Final\r\n\r\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\r\n\r\nApache Maven 3.9.3",
